Who We are and Why are we doing this? Meet some of the people behind World At Competition startup, the web platform that aims to empower youngsters with opportunities* worldwide.
We are small, young but motivated team that truly represents the world:  
Denys, Ukraine, CEO and Founder (currently in Portugal); 
Hasan, Bangladesh, Developer; 
Dima, Ukraine, Designer (currently in Bulgaria);

Yuri, Ukraine, International Coordinator (currently in Estonia);

Diletta, Italy, PR (currently in the USA). 
 Each of us has tried some kind of exchange program, volunteering, won a grant or achieved a scholarship. We also know how difficult and time-consuming it is to find relative opportunities. That is why the team came together to change that with one simple solution under World At Competition.
While we planned to deliver beta for the first users by November 3rd, a little problem seemed to undermine our mission.



Laptop or Nothing Back to the topic:  Our Designer lost any chance to recover his old laptop; Crowdfunding is the last option we try now (and it's always been; check out previous campaigns of Denys and Dima to understand the value they created with help of IndieGoGo community); This campaign is fast and relatively unprepared due to the urgency of the problem: if the Designer has no laptop, we would not be able to deliver a prototype on time;
However, if we do, you'll co-found a promising startup that will unite some of the brightest youths from around the Earth;
Only 7 days, only full amount, only with your help. 
   Choice explained Dima needs MacBook Pro with 15" Retina display as   it is perfect for design work due to its resolution, especially if you perform in tech and art (you want that amazing picture, right?); the power of this model resolves pain with big projects (and literally saves nerves and time);



Andy from My Tech Methods explains it in detail; the amount we raise reflects the price of the laptop at the local Apple store in Sofia, Bulgaria (where the Designer is currently based) and does not include IndieGoGo commission.






Invest in WAC because:


We are going to be a Spotify of opportunities (why not);
We aim big with a humble budget, still successfully;
We do good while planning on a massive return due to unique business model(s);

It is the Platform of Awesomeness. Invest in Awesomeness!


#GetMacForWAC and receive some cool, unique rewards (not plain T-shirts, ha).





All are real drawings by Dima aka Frost, WAC designer and simply cool, creative folk.

Other Ways You Can Help We know some of you are unable to help financially, but your support can be as big as sending a link to one friend or a community of same-minded people.
Besides, you can:  Join our Beta list; be the Early Bird and see us growing from the start;
Invite an organization that offers a scholarship or grant (could be a university or NGO/foundation) to become our partner and benefit from reaching even more potential candidates; Spread a word in your school or college; after all, it's all about passionate youth for whom we do all this;
Simply tweet #GetMacForWAC and let us know by adding @wac_startup!

Share the Chance

*Opportunities - here we mean grants, scholarships, volunteering, competitions, exchange programs, internships, conferences and many more to make the best out of professional and personal growth.BIG Thanks toFilippo Nardi (freestyler, Italy), Eda Engin (international student and EVS volunteer, Turkey), and incredible Pedro Queirós from Portugal for making the promo video possible and supporting WAC team throughout the time (he is also Adamastor staff member where everything happened).Also, thank you the WAC community, coordinators and simply people who share our mission. Without you there is no point of the whole thing.Denys thanks N. for even more inspiration.WAC is member and participant of
